From f8b782536ca316f4ec0a82e2fb304844d05c2a6b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "branch() prototype" <prototype@branch-syscall.local>
Date: Thu, 30 Apr 2026 23:01:39 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] branch: implement syscall and wire ioctls to branching
 filesystem

Implement the multiplexed branch(op, attr, size) syscall in
kernel/branch.c.

BR_CREATE:
  For each of N children, call vfs_ioctl(mount_fd, FS_IOC_BRANCH_CREATE)
  to ask the underlying branching filesystem (e.g. BranchFS) to create a
  fresh branch. The 128-byte branch name returned by the FS is copied to
  userspace via branch_names[i] and stashed in branch_member->name. Then
  fork N children; each receives its branch_id (1..N) as the syscall
  return value, with the parent getting 0 + child_pids[] filled.

BR_COMMIT:
  The first child to call BR_COMMIT wins via atomic_try_cmpxchg on the
  group's winner field. Winner's vfs_ioctl(ctl_fd, FS_IOC_BRANCH_COMMIT)
  merges the FS branch into the parent; the kernel then SIGKILLs all
  sibling tasks in the group. Losers see a non-zero winner and return
  -ESTALE without ever touching the FS.

BR_ABORT:
  vfs_ioctl(ctl_fd, FS_IOC_BRANCH_ABORT) discards the FS branch, then
  the calling task exits via do_exit(0).

Use get_task_struct() to pin sibling task pointers under the group
spinlock before SIGKILL, avoiding lock-order issues with sighand
->siglock.

Add CONFIG_BRANCH (default y), allocate syscall #470 in syscall_64.tbl,
declare sys_branch in linux/syscalls.h, and wire kernel/branch.o into
kernel/Makefile.

This commit only adds the syscall; the fork/exit hook required to
actually deliver branch_id to children and free branch_member on exit
is added in a follow-up commit so it can be reviewed separately.
